name: SSHLibrary 3.8.1rc1
body:
SSHLibrary 3.8.1rc1 is a new release that adds support for RF 5 and few more fixes . 
For more information see the [release notes](https://github.com/robotframework/SSHLibrary/blob/master/docs/SSHLibrary-3.8.1rc1.rst).

name: SSHLibrary 3.8.0
body: SSHLibrary 3.8.0 is a new release that adds glob pattern support to File/Directory Should (Not) Exist keywords but also has several enhancements and bugfixes. For more information see the [release notes](https://github.com/robotframework/SSHLibrary/blob/master/docs/SSHLibrary-3.8.0.rst).

name: SSHLibrary 3.0.0
body:
SSHLibrary 3.0.0 is a new release with Python 3 support and various other enhancements such as execute commands with sudo, regexp support for prompt and enhanced keyword documentation.

For more details about the release see the [release notes](https://github.com/robotframework/SSHLibrary/blob/master/docs/SSHLibrary-3.0.0.rst) and the [3.0.0 milestone](https://github.com/robotframework/SSHLibrary/milestone/4).

name: SSHLibrary 3.0.0rc1
body: The main new feature in SSHLibrary 3.0.0 is the support for Python 3. Another important feature is the possibility to use sudo to execute and start commands. For more details see the [full release notes](https://github.com/robotframework/SSHLibrary/blob/master/docs/SSHLibrary-3.0.0rc1.rst).

name: SSHLibrary 3.0.0a1
body: New major release with Python 3 support. For more details see the [full release notes](https://github.com/robotframework/SSHLibrary/blob/master/docs/SSHLibrary-3.0.0a1.rst).

name: SSHLibrary 2.1.3
body:
This release fixes compatibility with Paramiko 2.1.0 (#158). Thanks @raphaelcastaneda for the fix (#159)!

The easiest way to install this releases is using the standard

```
pip install --upgrade robotframework-sshlibrary
```

If you need to download and install the distribution manually, you can find it from [PyPI](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/robotframework-sshlibrary).

name: SSHLibrary 2.1.2
body:
This release fixes several Cygwin related problems and makes a few additions to internal APIs.

See all issues at [milestone 2.1.2](https://github.com/robotframework/SSHLibrary/issues?q=milestone%3A2.1.2).

Downloads are hosted at [PyPI](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/robotframework-sshlibrary/2.1.2).

name: SSHLibrary 2.1.1 - A micro release with a new function in programming API
body:
This release only adds a new method to internal client API to read until a regular expression occurs in output + given prefix. The method signature is: `def read_until_regexp_with_prefix(self, regexp, prefix)`. There are no other changes.

See all issues at [milestone 2.1.1](https://github.com/robotframework/SSHLibrary/issues?q=milestone%3A2.1.1).

Downloads are hosted at [PyPI](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/robotframework-sshlibrary/2.1.1).

name: SSHLibrary 2.1 - New release with some backwards incompatible changes
body:
This release removes the deprecated argument path_separator from `Get File` and `Put File`. Paramiko will also no longer try to use ssh agent in authentication. There are also several bug fixes.

See all issues at [milestone 2.1](https://github.com/robotframework/SSHLibrary/issues?q=milestone%3A2.1).

Downloads are hosted at [PyPI](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/robotframework-sshlibrary/2.1).
